author: Justin Harp
title: TV show ratings: Sleepy Hollow falls again, as Grey's Anatomy rebounds on Thursday - Sleepy Hollow Cult -
text: CBS's coverage of the Atlanta Falcons vs. New Orleans Saints game dominated the key 18-49 demographic with 4.5 on Thursday (October 15), according to Nielsen figures.Thursday Night Football racked up 4.9 (14.78m) at 8.30pm, well ahead of any competition. Â© Fox ABC's Grey's Anatomy was up two-tenths of a point to 2.3 (6.74m) at 8pm, before Scandal and How to Get Away with Murder dropped to 2.4 (8.06m) at 9pm and 2.0 (6.81m) at 10pm respectively.Fox's Sleepy Hollow reached a low of 0.8 (2.97m) at 9pm on Fox, after Bones took 1.1 (5.79m) at 8pm.Heroes Reborn slid to 1.1 (4.01m) at 8pm on NBC. Later, The Blacklist garnered 1.4 (6.93m) at 9pm and The Player pulled in 0.7 (3.99m) at 10pm.Over on The CW, The Vampire Diaries was steady with 0.6 (1.40m) at 8pm while The Originals rose a tenth to 0.5 (1.12m) at 9pm.
